          "text": "Below is a **1-page English resume draft** tuned for a **Mercor – Bilingual Software Engineer** application, using your existing background but shifting the emphasis from finance-specific ML to **AI-native software engineering, automation, deployment, and cross-functional execution**. The source material comes from your uploaded career document. fileciteturn0file0L1-L6 fileciteturn0file0L18-L24\n\n---\n\n# HEEWON OH  \nSeoul, South Korea  \nGitHub: `github.com/unohee` | Hugging Face: `huggingface.co/intrect`\n\n## Bilingual Software Engineer  \nAI-native software engineer with hands-on experience building LLM applications, agentic developer workflows, data pipelines, and production-facing automation systems. Strong at turning ambiguous operational problems into working software: defining workflows, integrating APIs and data sources, shipping prototypes quickly, and stabilizing them for real use. Comfortable working across research, backend systems, deployment, and user-facing automation. Fluent in Korean and able to work in English technical environments. fileciteturn0file0L18-L24 fileciteturn0file0L45-L62\n\n## CORE SKILLS\n**Languages:** Python, JavaScript/Node.js, Bash, SQL fileciteturn0file0L15-L16  \n**AI / LLM:** OpenAI/Anthropic-style API workflows, RAG, FAISS, SBERT, SFT/DPO fine-tuning, Tool Calling, vLLM, llama-cpp, GGUF/ONNX, MLX fileciteturn0file0L11-L15  \n**Backend / Infra:** FastAPI, GraphQL, Redis, Nginx, Docker/OrbStack, SQLite WAL, GitHub Actions, WebSocket systems fileciteturn0file0L13-L15  \n**Deployment / Ops:** Cloudflare Tunnel, Tailscale, RunPod Serverless, remote service operations, lightweight production deployment  \n**Domains:** LLM applications, workflow automation, agent systems, real-time data services, audio/ML research\n\n## EXPERIENCE\n\n### Independent AI / Software Engineer  \n**2024 – Present**\nBuilt and operated multiple end-to-end AI systems spanning LLM workflows, real-time backend services, ML pipelines, and deployment infrastructure.\n\n**STONKS — LLM-powered research and decision automation platform**  \n- Designed and built a full-stack platform that automated multi-step analysis workflows by combining LLM tool use, search, sentiment analysis, structured reporting, and real-time market data. fileciteturn0file0L82-L99  \n- Implemented a Claude API + GraphQL tool-calling workflow, integrated 42 API routers, and built a 12-tab dashboard with remote access and monitoring. fileciteturn0file0L82-L99  \n- Built feedback loops to track downstream outcomes and tune scoring logic based on real-world performance rather than offline metrics alone. fileciteturn0file0L100-L107  \n- Delivered the project as a solo engineer: **506,900 LOC, 1,578 commits, 2,400+ hours**. fileciteturn0file0L63-L67 fileciteturn0file0L107-L108  \n\n**VELA — domain-adapted LLM and report generation system**  \n- Fine-tuned a Qwen2.5-7B based model using **36,713 SFT samples** and **24,779 DPO pairs**, then built supporting retrieval and report-generation infrastructure around it. fileciteturn0file0L45-L55  \n- Built RAG workflows using FAISS, BM25/FTS5 optimization, reasoning traces, and confidence-aware structured output generation. fileciteturn0file0L55-L62  \n- Deployed inference through quantized runtimes and serverless infrastructure, including RunPod Serverless and Apple Silicon MLX support. fileciteturn0file0L53-L60  \n\n**OpenSwarm — multi-agent coding workflow orchestrator**  \n- Built an open-source orchestration system for Claude Code CLI with worker/reviewer execution patterns, long-term vector memory, and issue-driven automation. fileciteturn0file0L121-L126  \n- Project gained external traction with **232 GitHub stars** and **20 forks**. fileciteturn0file0L121-L126  \n\n**Data infrastructure and deployment**  \n- Built large-scale ingestion and cleaning pipelines for structured and unstructured datasets, including automated collection, parsing, embedding, deduplication, and internal API serving. fileciteturn0file0L127-L142  \n- Operated remote/internal services using **Tailscale + Cloudflare Tunnel**, and deployed inference workloads through **serverless GPU infrastructure**.  \n- Packaged services with Docker/Nginx and optimized for lightweight, cost-aware operations. fileciteturn0file0L13-L15\n\n### Lecturer, Media Art / Music Programming  \n**Seoul Institute of the Arts** | 2021 – 2026  \n**Howon University** | 2022 – 2025  \n- Taught media art, music programming, and interactive systems to university students. fileciteturn0file0L5-L10  \n- Developed strong communication skills translating technical concepts for non-engineering audiences.  \n- Worked across creative technology, software, and education in bilingual/cross-disciplinary contexts.\n\n## EDUCATION\n**M.A., Multimedia** — Dongguk University, 2022 fileciteturn0file0L1-L4  \n**B.Sc., Music Computing** — Goldsmiths, University of London, 2016 fileciteturn0file0L1-L4  \n\n## PUBLICATIONS / RESEARCH\n- *Multidimensional Analysis and Visualization of Audio Datasets*, Journal of Digital Contents Society, 2025. fileciteturn0file0L3-L5  \n- *ArtifactNet: AI-Generated Music Detection* — patent filed and ISMIR 2026 submission in progress. fileciteturn0file0L5-L6 fileciteturn0file0L38-L44\n\n## ADDITIONAL\n- 10+ years of professional sound design experience, including work for brands such as Louis Vuitton and thisisneverthat. fileciteturn0file0L5-L6  \n- Strong fit for roles requiring bilingual communication, fast prototyping, AI tooling, and independent execution across ambiguous technical problems.\n\n---\n\n몇 군데는 **Mercor용으로 더 공격적으로 바꿀 수 있다**.  \n특히 제목과 첫 줄은 아래 셋 중 하나가 더 잘 먹힐 수 있다.\n\n### Option A\n**Bilingual Software Engineer | AI Automation, LLM Systems, Backend Infrastructure**\n\n### Option B\n**Software Engineer | Bilingual (Korean/English) | LLM Apps, Agent Workflows, Production Systems**\n\n### Option C\n**AI-Native Software Engineer | Bilingual | Python, LLM Systems, Workflow Automation**\n\n그리고 Mercor 쪽이면 보통 **읽는 속도**가 중요해서, 실제 제출본은 여기서 더 줄여서:\n- publication 2줄\n- lecturer 2줄\n- STONKS/VELA/OpenSwarm 각 3 bullet\n정도로 압축하는 게 낫다.\n\n원하면 바로 이어서 **Mercor 제출형 ultra-compact version**으로 15~20줄짜리 최종본으로 다시 줄여주겠다."
